rdf:Description.lla:note: Cert.no. 34537. Note by master on front of crew list: Voyage terminated 1878-02-10 "Abandoned at Sea", no explanation. Home address given on record 2.

rdf:Description.bio:place: Vessel [illegible word written across] Abandoned at Sea

rdf:Description.lla:note: Desertion confimed by Consul at Pernambuco
Note in Wages on Discharge column: "In debt to Ship"
Cert.no. 34537. Note across blanks on crew list by Master: "All this blank unknown - articles left on paying off at Customs Falmouth E. Lewis". Info supplied in [] from Record 1.
Dates of Mate leaving and joining ship confused, not clearly written within columns

Age given as 17 on Record 1. Some confusion as to first name - mostly spelt Ioas with bar across top, here spelt Joas with tilda above - therefore Jonas? Middle name Francisco given in Consulate note on Record 1.
